      "content": "The consistent negative variance across all SKUs suggests a systemic issue rather than random theft, likely pointing to receiving errors where items are logged as issued but not fully counted upon arrival. Systematic miscounting at shift changeovers or unrecorded internal transfers could also explain why the discrepancies happen every week with similar magnitudes. To resolve this, I recommend implementing a cycle count protocol specifically for high-item-electronic components and conducting a physical footprint count of the receiving and storage zones.",
